Package gui.view

Class Matchfield

java.lang.Object
gui.view.Matchfield
public class Matchfield
extends java.lang.Object
This class implements the grid pane with the matchfield and offers methods to fill the pane with image views of the ground, the buildings and the moving objects.
Author:
Judith

    • fillWithField1

      public void fillWithField1​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Integer> indexes, java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,​java.lang.Boolean> completed, int stateOfGrowth)
      This method is used when reloading the game. If parts of field 1 have been processed before saving it sets the correct image views to the grid pane.
      Parameters:
      indexes - HashMap of the class FieldTile that holds the matching indexes of the moving object on the matchfield and the index of the node on the grid pane
      completed - HashMap of the class FieldTile that holds the indexes of each tile of the field and if it is already processed
      stateOfGrowth - state of growth of field 1

    • initializeMovingObject

      protected void initializeMovingObject​(int selectedObject, int column, int row)
      This method initializes the moving object on the field. It uses the methods setImageView() and setTileOfObject().
      Parameters:
      selectedObject - integer of the selected moving object that is shown on the matchfield, handed to the method getTheRightImageView()
      column - index of the column to which the image view is set, handed to the method setTileOfObject()
      row - index of the column to which the image view is set, handed to the method setTileOfObject()

    • initializeSecondMovingObject

      public void initializeSecondMovingObject​(int selectedObject, int column, int row)
      This method initializes a second object on the field. It uses the methods setImageView() and setTileOfObject(). Actually this image view isn't meant to move around.
      Parameters:
      selectedObject - integer of the selected moving object that is shown on the matchfield, handed to the method getTheRightImageView()
      column - index of the column to which the image view is set, handed to the method setTileOfObject()
      row - index of the column to which the image view is set, handed to the method setTileOfObject()
